description:
It's the first complete stories chronicling the wild adventures of the Luchadores Five, Tequila and Tikitis, collected for the first time! Also includes bonus behind-the-scenes artwork. It's perfect way to sample the hilarious mix of superheroes and masked wrestling that received a 2008 Eisner Award nomination!

160 Pages.

Translated by Natacha Ruck, Ken Grobe, and Hicham Benkirane.

Chapter Titles

  • LUCHADORES FIVE (originally published in issues #1-2)
  • TEQUILA (originally published in issues #2-5)
  • THE TIKITIS (originally published in issues #3-5)
  • LOS TRIPLICADOS (originally published in issue #5)
  • LUCHA LIBRE: The Toys (ad)

description: Harley confronts a gathering of rebellion-minded Joker devotees in one of the late criminal’s old hideouts and doesn’t know quite what to make of them. Batwoman tries to break things up. And just when it looks like things are under control, tragedy strikes.
name: Revolutionary

volume.name: Injustice: Gods Among Us Year Five

description: Raven and Cyborg create a pair of spooky-looking leggings from a pattern in one of Raven’s arcane books. But Robin’s in for quite the fright when he tries on these “Scaredy Pants”! Then, when Titans East instigates a friendly softball outing, Robin sees a vast conspiracy by Speedy to undermine his team. And when his mania spreads to the other Titans, they’re going to turn a friendly game into a high-stakes death match.
name: Scaredy Pants

description:
Judge Dredd; The Lion’s Den by Michael Carroll, Henry Flint, and Annie Parkhouse; Lawless: Of Munce and Men by Dan Abnett, Phil Winslade, and Ellie De Ville; movie sequel Dredd: Dust by Arthur Wyatt, Ben Willsher and Simon Bowland; Realm of the Damned: Tenebris Deos by Alec Worley and Pye Parr – plus features on 2000 AD’s Free Comic Book Day issue, Eric Powell, Star Trek: The Classic UK Comics, and an obituary of Tony Luke. And in the bagged graphic novel this month, concentrated Thrill-power in four Tharg’s 3rillers – short, snappy threepart self-contained stories across a wide range of genres, from creeping horror to explosive future-war, don’t miss this first collection of amazing tales from creators Alec Worley (Realm of the Damned), Mike Dowling (Unfollow), Tom Taylor (Wolverine), Jon Davis-Hunt (Clean Room), Boo Cook (Elephantmen), T.C. Eglington (Outlier), David Baillie (Red Thorn) and Inaki Miranda (Catwoman)!

Cover: Ben Willsher

  • Judge Dredd - Dust To Dust (Part One) (Michael Carroll - Henry Flint)
  • Realm of the Damned - Tenebris Dios (Part Three) (Alec Worley - Simon Parr)
  • Lawless - Of Munce & Men (Part One) (Dan Abnett - Phil Winslade)
  • Dredd - Dust (Part Five) (Arthur Wyatt - Ben Willsher)

Graphic Novel - The Best of Tharg's 3rillers Volume One

description:
Saved from the scrap heap by billionaire Howard Quartz, sewer droid Ro-Jaws and battle-weary war-bot Hammerstein became part of Ro-Busters - Quartz's international, robotic rescue squad. Plunged into situations far too dangerous for human beings to handle, the robotic duo need to maintain a 100% success rate, or face the threat of being dismantled by the sadistic battle tank Mek-Quake!

Written by Pat Mills (The ABC Warriors) and featuring several British comic art luminaries, including Dave Gibbons (Watchmen), Ian Kennedy (Commando) and Kevin O'Neill (League of Extraordinary Gentlemen), this first volume includes all of the original Starlord strips and colour spreads.
name: Volume One

volume.name: Ro-Busters the Complete Nuts and Bolts

description: Hola, amigos! Brian and Marcos here, excited to share that our new WALKING DEAD one-shot is finally available exclusively online at PanelSyndicate.com! We’re stunned and grateful that Robert Kirkman let us tell this particular story, which is firmly set in the continuity of his and Charlie Adlard’s beloved series. “The Alien" sheds light on a corner of their undead universe we never dreamed they’d let us reveal, and you can download the entire 31-page (!) black-and-white special at PanelSyndicate.com for any price you think is fair. Robert is very generously allowing us to keep 100% of whatever readers like you contribute, so thanks for helping to keep our site alive! - BKV & MM
name: The Alien
